Title : Thomas C. Salamone
Text : '''Thomas C. Salamone''' (March 28, 1927 &ndash; April 15, 2014) was an American politician and businessman.

Born in [[Waterbury, Connecticut]], Salamone served in the [[United States Navy]] during [[World War II]] and went to [[Post University]]. He owned Salamone Insurance Agency. Salamone served in the [[Connecticut House of Representatives]], from [[Wolcott, Connecticut]], as a [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democrat]], from 1963 until 1971.<ref>[http://www.chaseparkwaymemorial.com/fh/obituaries/obituary.cfm?o_id=2480679&fh_id=12319 Thomas C. Salamone-obituary]</ref><ref>[http://www.cslib.org/conngares.asp Members of the Connecticut General  Assembly] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071007105422/http://www.cslib.org/conngares.asp |date=2007-10-07 }}</ref>

